{"author":{"id":"27a92b445112509f896fbafb1295a63babb443b0af855b44b6dc09c14110e240"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1562580035,"nonce":"caKGPm3OOlCd4h5YMh6LGmqFV6Q=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDUwOTE2MjQ0NA==","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/178#issuecomment-509162444"},"message":"Nothing to do with #103 \n\nWhat's happening is rather simple. git-bug need to store on disk a few temporary files (pre-compiled bugs and identities, clocks ...). You can safely delete those and git-bug will recompute them next launch, but it does need a place to store them.\n\nCurrently, git-bug store those file in `.git/git-bug/`. The `.git` folder is found using the `git rev-parse --show-top-level` command, which notably doesn't work for a bare repository or if you are already inside the .git folder.\n\nSo nothing really preventing from fixing this problem, we just need to come up to the good solution.","files":null},{"type":2,"timestamp":1562580267,"nonce":"zjyVsp2XwvvPamKebsdnZi+p27o=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE3OlJlbmFtZWRUaXRsZUV2ZW50MjQ2NTYwMDkzNg=="},"title":"git-bug doesn'y work in bare repository","was":"git-bug doesn't work in bare repository"},{"type":5,"timestamp":1562580272,"nonce":"9GB40PfydGEFVKaL3MFyhO121Ds=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDI0NjU2MDExNzU="},"added":["kind/bug"],"removed":[]}]}